definition: thigh/part of a whole/portion of a sum/(stock) share/strand of a thread/low-level administrative unit, translated as "section" or "department" etc, ranked below 科[ke1]/classifier for long winding things like ropes, rivers etc/classifier for smoke, smells etc: thread, puff, whiff/classifier for bands of people, gangs etc/classifier for sudden forceful actions

sentences.english: By using a binocular, i saw her butt cleavage.
sentences.chinese: 用望远镜，我看见她的股沟了。

sentences.english: He felt a warm trickle of sweat running down the crack to his anus.
sentences.chinese: 他觉得一股热热的汗水沿着股沟向下流。

sentences.english: Executives at Google have said little about the intrusions and would not comment for this article.
sentences.chinese: 股沟的执行官对入侵三敛其口，不愿对本文发表评论。

sentences.english: She also allowed Google to examine her personal computer at the company's request.
sentences.chinese: 她还依照股沟公司的请求允许他们检查她的个人电脑。

sentences.english: Its employees in China are still going to work, she said.
sentences.chinese: 她说，股沟在中国的员工仍在工作。
